  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6157d4a 2023-02-03T00:05:03.034611Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI've created a reproduction here: https://github.com/Kooshaba/forge_bug_repro\r\n\r\nIt uses an ownable storage contract called by a library from a script. There are two functions in the library: one public, one internal. When using `startPrank` and calling the storage contract via the public method, the `msg.sender` is the address of the library. When using the internal method, it correctly mocks the `msg.sender` to be the pranked address.",
